    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <head>No. 553.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Christiancy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 12,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 144.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        282, and to approve the tenor of your letter (a copy of which you inclose)
                        to Mr. Kauffmann, consular agent, &amp;c., on the question of the right of
                        Peruvian or Chilian authorities to levy forced or extraordinary
                        contributions upon American citizens in Peru.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
